<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,393,1210]" pageId="4" pageNumber="265">
Usually flattened, rarely subcylindrical species; elytra more or less parallel-sided, covering lateral parts of ventrites from the dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[405,557,429,454]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1854,1877]" captionTargetBox="[160,1426,239,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,230,1801]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Anthaxia, dorsal aspect. 1—Anthaxia (Anthaxia) fulgurans (Schrank), male, 4.5 mm; 2—A. (A.) plicata plicata Kiesenwetter, female, 5.1 mm; 3—A. (A.) salicis salicis (Fabricius), male, 4.1 mm; 4—A. (A.) malachitica Abeille, male, 2.1 mm; 5—A. (A.) stepanovi Richter, holotype, 3.0 mm; 6—A. (Cratomerus) hungarica hungarica (Scopoli), male, 12.0 mm; 7—the same, female, 13.5 mm; 8—A. (Haplanthaxia) dispar Kerremans, male, 7.5 mm; 9—A. (H.) cichorii (Olivier), male, 5.1 mm; 10—A. (H.) kneuckeri zabranskyi Bílý, male, 5.1 mm; 11—A. (A.) cashmirensis Obenberger, male, 8.5 mm; 12—A. (Melanthaxia) godeti Gory &amp; Laporte, male, 4.7 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2599420/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="265">Figs. 1–5, 11</figureCitation>
), elytral epipleura wide, not reaching elytral apex or very narrow (namely in middle of elytral length), almost missing in small, subcylindrical species (
<figureCitation box="[987,1073,465,490]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–39" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1832,1855]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,742,1802]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[150,1437,733,1811]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 25–39. Anthaxia, subhumeral lobe (not in scale). 25—Anthaxia (Richteraxia) amplithorax Kerremans, white arrow indicates “lock&quot; in humeral callosity; 26—A. (Anthaxia) salicis salicis (Fabricius); 27—A. (A.) fulgurans (Schrank); 28—A. (A.) plicata plicata Kiesenwetter; 29—A. (A.) stepanovi Richter, holotype; 30—A. (Cratomerus) hungarica hungarica (Scopoli); 31—A. (Haplanthaxia) cichorii (Olivier); 32—A. (H.) caseyi Obenberger; 33—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans; 34—A. (Richteraxia) angustipennis (Klug); 35—A. (Melanthaxia) quadripunctata (Linnaeus); 36—A. (M.) kochi Obenberger; 37—A. (Merocratus) insulaecola Obenberger; 38—A. (Thailandia.) rondoni Baudon; 39—A. (Capanthzaxia..) hilaris Gory." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2599424/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="265">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); subhumeral lobe very weak or absent (
<figureCitation box="[239,377,501,526]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–39" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1832,1855]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,742,1802]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[150,1437,733,1811]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 25–39. Anthaxia, subhumeral lobe (not in scale). 25—Anthaxia (Richteraxia) amplithorax Kerremans, white arrow indicates “lock&quot; in humeral callosity; 26—A. (Anthaxia) salicis salicis (Fabricius); 27—A. (A.) fulgurans (Schrank); 28—A. (A.) plicata plicata Kiesenwetter; 29—A. (A.) stepanovi Richter, holotype; 30—A. (Cratomerus) hungarica hungarica (Scopoli); 31—A. (Haplanthaxia) cichorii (Olivier); 32—A. (H.) caseyi Obenberger; 33—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans; 34—A. (Richteraxia) angustipennis (Klug); 35—A. (Melanthaxia) quadripunctata (Linnaeus); 36—A. (M.) kochi Obenberger; 37—A. (Merocratus) insulaecola Obenberger; 38—A. (Thailandia.) rondoni Baudon; 39—A. (Capanthzaxia..) hilaris Gory." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2599424/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="265">Figs. 26–29</figureCitation>
), lateral sides of elytra not or very weakly emarginate posterior to subhumeral lobe (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 25–39" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1832,1855]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,742,1802]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[150,1437,733,1811]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 25–39. Anthaxia, subhumeral lobe (not in scale). 25—Anthaxia (Richteraxia) amplithorax Kerremans, white arrow indicates “lock&quot; in humeral callosity; 26—A. (Anthaxia) salicis salicis (Fabricius); 27—A. (A.) fulgurans (Schrank); 28—A. (A.) plicata plicata Kiesenwetter; 29—A. (A.) stepanovi Richter, holotype; 30—A. (Cratomerus) hungarica hungarica (Scopoli); 31—A. (Haplanthaxia) cichorii (Olivier); 32—A. (H.) caseyi Obenberger; 33—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans; 34—A. (Richteraxia) angustipennis (Klug); 35—A. (Melanthaxia) quadripunctata (Linnaeus); 36—A. (M.) kochi Obenberger; 37—A. (Merocratus) insulaecola Obenberger; 38—A. (Thailandia.) rondoni Baudon; 39—A. (Capanthzaxia..) hilaris Gory." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2599424/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="265">Fig. 26– 29</figureCitation>
); pronotal sculpture consisting of simple, polygonal cells with or without central grains, lateral margins of pronotum often with oblique or longitudinal rugae (
<figureCitation box="[752,840,573,598]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–54" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1837,1860]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,353,1806]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1435,339,1815]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 40–54. Anthaxia, pronotal sculpture (not in scale). 40—Anthaxia (Anthaxia) fulgurans (Schrank); 41—A. (A.) salicis salicis (Fabricius); 42—A. (A.) manca (Fabricius); 43—A. (Melanthaxia) nigrojubata nigrojubata Roubal; 44—A. (Cratomerus) hungarica hungarica (Scopoli); 45—A. (Haplanthaxia) cichorii (Olivier); 46—A. (H.) kneuckeri zabranskyi Bílý; 47—A. (H.) pumila (Klug); 48—A. (Richteraxia) angustipennis (Klug); 49—A. (R.) marginifera metallescens Bílý; 50— A. (Merocratus) tamdaoensis Bílý; 51—A. (Thailandia) rondoni Baudon; 52—A. (Capanthaxia) capensis Kerremans; 53—A. (Cap.) aterrima Kerremans; 54—A. (Cap.) sulcicollis Obenberger." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2599428/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="265">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
), in some species-groups pronotum with concentric rugae (
